ferrocarrilesDeAmericaDelSur.railways

Class Basket

  • java.lang.Object
    • ferrocarrilesDeAmericaDelSur.railways.Basket

  • public class Basket
extends java.lang.Object
    Models baskets for the railway system. Baskets can have stones put in them or removed from them, and can be checked for stones.
    Version:
    December 2019
    Author:
    Hugh Osborne

      • putStoneInBasket

      • putStone

        void putStone()
       throws ProgrammingError
        Put a stone in the basket. The capacity of baskets is unlimited. This is the method called by a railway, and includes a delay and a trace.
        Throws:
        ProgrammingError - if the specified railway is not registered with a railway system.

      • takeStoneFromBasket

        private void takeStoneFromBasket()
                          throws ProgrammingError
        Remove a stone from the basket.
        Throws:
        ProgrammingError - if there is no stone to remove.

      • takeStone

        void takeStone()
        throws ProgrammingError
        Remove a stone from the basket. This is the method called by a railway, and includes a delay and a trace.
        Throws:
        ProgrammingError - if the specified railway is not registered with a railway system.

      • basketHasStone

        Check if the basket contains at least one stone.

          throws ProgrammingError
        Check if the basket contains at least one stone. This is the method called by a railway, and includes a delay and a trace.
